  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Purchaser / Buyer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Negotiate and secure optimal pricing for first article items and regular production materials.</li><li>Provide mentorship and guidance to junior staff on procurement activities</li><li>Facilitate first article approval and maintain accurate purchase information records.</li><li>Collaborate with suppliers, Quality, and Production teams to resolve quality, delivery, and supply issues.</li><li>Generate shortage reports in SAP, prepare delivery schedules, and communicate them to suppliers in a timely manner.</li><li>Ensure rejected items are either replaced with correct parts or appropriately credited via issued Credit Notes.</li><li>Conduct timely audits of existing suppliers and assess potential new suppliers for qualification.</li><li>Ensure compliance with company Quality, EHS policies, and safety regulations, and promptly report any EHS-related concerns.</li></ul><p><br /><br /></p><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma or Degree in Engineering or Supply Chain Management.</li><li>International sourcing experience is strongly preferred.</li><li>Proficient in reading and interpreting technical drawings and specifications.</li><li>Solid understanding of legal terminology related to supplier/vendor agreements and contracts.</li><li>Experience in BOM cost management and part/product costing analysis.</li><li>Proven ability to manage multiple projects, set clear goals, and ensure successful execution of commodity strategies.</li><li>Strong analytical capability, with proficiency in data interpretation and dashboards.</li><li>Advanced proficiency in ERP systems and Microsoft Office, Excel.</li></ul>",
